This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with the effectiveness of social explanations in recommender systems. It could also belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category as it involves the use of social networks in the recommendation process. Additionally, the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category is relevant as the study involves user behavior and decision-making. The Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category could also be relevant as the study involves analyzing the language used in social explanations. Finally, the Social and Behavioral Sciences (cs.SOC) sub-category could be relevant as the study involves understanding the impact of social factors on user behavior.
